The paper deals with game theory, social influence, and trust networks, which are all topics that fall under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). Additionally, the paper explores the effects of social networks on agents' behavior, which is a topic that falls under the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Societal Computing). The paper also uses temporal logic to express agents' goals, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses game-theoretic solution concepts such as Nash equilibrium and winning strategies, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
